trans-unit.source: An RNN cell, in the most abstract setting, is anything that has a state and performs some operation that takes a matrix of inputs. This operation results in an output matrix with self.output_size columns. If self.state_size is an integer, this operation also results in a new state matrix with self.state_size columns. If self.state_size is a (possibly nested tuple of) TensorShape object(s), then it should return a matching structure of Tensors having shape [batch_size].concatenate(s) for each s in self.batch_size.
trans-unit.target: 在最抽象的情况下，RNN单元是具有状态并执行某些需要输入矩阵的操作的任何事物。此操作将生成带有 self.output_size 列的输出矩阵。如果 self.state_size 是整数，则此操作还将导致具有 self.state_size 列的新状态矩阵。如果 self.state_size 是TensorShape对象（一个或多个）（的可能是嵌套元组），则它应该返回张量的具有形状的匹配结构 [batch_size].concatenate(s) 为每个 s 在 self.batch_size 。

trans-unit.target: 对变量引用进行稀疏更新。

trans-unit.target: 将梯度更新应用于嵌入表。

trans-unit.source: Applies the normalization configuration in-place to a batch of inputs.
trans-unit.target: 将原地的标准化配置应用于一批输入。

trans-unit.source: Applies the rectified linear unit activation function.
trans-unit.target: 应用整流后的线性单元激活函数。

trans-unit.source: Applies the sigmoid activation function. For small values (<-5), sigmoid returns a value close to zero, and for large values (>5) the result of the function gets close to 1.
trans-unit.target: 应用S型激活功能。对于较小的值（<-5）， sigmoid 将返回接近零的值，对于较大的值（> 5），函数的结果将接近1。

trans-unit.source: Applies the sigmoid activation function. The sigmoid function is defined as 1 divided by (1 + exp(-x)). It's curve is like an "S" and is like a smoothed version of the Heaviside (Unit Step Function) function. For small values (<-5) the sigmoid returns a value close to zero and for larger values (>5) the result of the function gets close to 1.
trans-unit.target: 应用S型激活功能。乙状结肠功能定义为1除以（1 + exp（-x））。它的曲线像“ S”形，就像Heaviside（单位阶跃函数）函数的平滑版本。对于较小的值（<-5），S型将返回接近零的值；对于较大的值（> 5），S函数的结果将接近1。

trans-unit.source: Applies upper_bound(sorted_search_values, values) along each row.
trans-unit.target: 沿着每一行应用 upper_bound(sorted_search_values,values)。
